Srv:
Defines business logic and expose APIS
Typical Structure
srv/
 ├── service.cds
 ├── service.js   (or .ts)
 └── handlers/
Key contents:
 .cds → Service definitions (OData endpoints) 
 .js/.ts → Custom logic (event handlers)
Example:
using { my.bookshop as db } from '../db/schema';

service CatalogService {
  entity Books as projection on db.Books;
}
Example handler:
module.exports = (srv) => {
  srv.on('READ', 'Books', async (req) => {
    return [{ ID: 1, title: "CAP Guide", stock: 10 }];
  });
};
