connecting cap to sap hana
step 1: Add HANA Dependency
npm install @sap/cds-hana
step 2: update package.json
"cds": {
  "requires": {
    "db": {
      "kind": "hana"
    }
  }
}
Step 3: Add HANA Configuration
{
  "requires": {
    "db": {
      "kind": "hana",
      "credentials": {
        "host": "<hana-host>",
        "port": "443",
        "user": "<username>",
        "password": "<password>",
        "schema": "BOOKSHOP"
      }
    }
  }
}
Step 4: Deploy to HANA
BUILD ARTIFACTS
BASH
cds build --for hana
deploy
cds deploy --to hana
Step 5: RUN WITH HANA
Cds run
Now cap uses sap hana instead of sqlite database.
End to end request flow:
GET /catalog/Books
1. UI Layer (app/)
•	User clicks "View Books" 
•	Sends HTTP request to:

Service Layer (srv/)
•	catalog-service.cds exposes endpoint 
•	CAP runtime intercepts request 
Note: If custom logic exists:
srv.on('READ', 'Books', ...)
CAP Runtime
•	Converts OData → SQL 
•	Applies: 
o	Filters 
o	Projections 
o	Associations 

4. Database Layer (db/)
•	Query executed on: 
o	SQLite (default) OR 
o	SAP HANA (production)
Example SQL:
SELECT * FROM Books;
Response Back
•	Data → CAP → OData JSON → UI 
{
  "value": [
    { "ID": 1, "title": "Harry Potter", "stock": 100 }
  ]
}

